# Nyckla Project Rules

All conventions are in @CLAUDE.md. Follow it for:
- Auth: `getCurrentUser()` from `lib/auth-utils.ts`, never look up by email
- Entity scoping: always filter by `entityId: user.activeOrganisationId`
- Encryption: `lib/entity-encryption.ts` — `getEntityKey` / `encryptWithEntityKey` / `decryptWithEntityKey`
- Server actions: `ActionResult<T>` shape, `revalidatePath`, `prisma.$transaction` for multi-step writes
- UI: shadcn/ui + Tabler Icons only (`@tabler/icons-react`)
- Borrowers: use `getBorrowerDetails` / `createBorrowerWithAffiliation` from `lib/borrower-utils.ts`

## Cursor-Specific: Responsive Dialogs

For all user-facing dialogs: use `ResponsiveDialog` from `@/components/ui/responsive-dialog`.
It renders as `Dialog` on desktop and `Drawer` on mobile (<768px) automatically.

## Slash Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/code-review` | Review against conventions (functionality, security, project rules) |
| `/check-entity-isolation` | Verify Prisma/entityId filtering, no `supabase.from()` |
| `/feature-workflow` | Branch → implement → test → push checklist |
